nodes.text: The Freedom of Naboo was a regular celebration held on the planet Naboo to commemorate the Battle of Naboo.

Prior to the Invasion of Naboo, the edges of the Lianorm Swamp on Naboo were considered the dividing line between the Naboo and the Gungan people, and were something of a no-man's-land populated by outcasts such as Jar Jar Binks. Following the unification of the two peoples, the Freedom of Naboo celebrations were held regularly for years following the battle, taking place on the swamp edges.
